snippet.textDisplay: Not really obsolete. They have a strong competitor now. Many games still prefer the higher OC to reach top framerates. Decisions have become a lot harder, but Intel is not obsolete. And nobody should want Intel to be obsolete. As Intel needed a competitive AMD to get out of their comfort zone, now AMD needs to be kept in check by Intel, otherwise you get Nvidia's crappy attitude and pricing. The good thing is that AMD will now have more money and be able to focus on the high end gpus as well to eventually even out with Nvidia.
